# Workflow (Timeless Electronix)

## 1. Orient

- Use root [`AI-DOCS-NAVIGATION.md`](../../AI-DOCS-NAVIGATION.md) to decide which `docs/` folders to read for the task.
- For ongoing work, check [`docs/06-Development/`](../../docs/06-Development/) (`tasks.md`, `progress.md` when you are tracking work there).
- If there is application code, follow patterns already in the tree before introducing new ones.

## 2. Plan

- Tie product intent to `docs/03-PRDs`, system shape to `docs/04-Architecture`, and UI to `docs/05-Design` when those places hold the real spec (not empty placeholders).
- If scope, security, or architecture is unclear or could contradict the written docs, ask the user before proceeding.

## 3. Implement

- Extend existing layout and conventions; avoid parallel stacks or duplicate patterns without a reason documented in `docs/`.

## 4. Verify

- If the repo defines checks (scripts, CI, etc.), run them and fix failures. Do not invent commands that are not in this repository.

## 5. Write it back

- After substantive work, update `docs/06-Development/tasks.md` and `docs/06-Development/progress.md` when those files are part of how this project tracks work.
- If you change how or what we test, note it in `docs/07-Tests` when that folder is in use.
